			<ns0:name>kschi...@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/108470876877739532758/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">The PNaCl bitcode reader/writer are copies of the LLVM bitcode reader/writer.

In several places, the writer emits LLVM enumerated values into the bitcode. This is problematic in that many of these enumerations are located in other directories, and do not (necessarily) have comments that reordering and/or deleting elements will break the bitcode reader/writers.

The code should be modified to (a) detect when an enumeration value has been removed, and (b) make sure that element reordering (or insertion) does not effect the bitcode.

The best way to handle this is to create separate enumerations in the PNaCl bitcode directory with appropriate comments on editing. Then, write encode/decode functions for each of these enumerations that convert the LLVM enumeration to the PNaCl bitcode enumeration.

Note that this solution will detect deleted enumerated values by failing to compile.</ns0:content><ns0:updated>2013-06-19T16:55:33.000Z</ns0:updated><ns0:published>2013-06-17T16:12:39.000Z</ns0:published><ns2:status>Started</ns2:status><ns2:owner>
